CenterSquare Investment Management

U.S. AND GLOBAL REAL ESTATE INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT

VIEW BOUTIQUE SITE

















 





1987


ESTABLISHED 

4
location

PHILADELPHIA, NEWPORT BEACH, LONDON, SINGAPORE









OVERVIEW
Founded in 1987, CenterSquare Investment Management is a real asset manager focused on listed and private equity real estate and listed infrastructure investments, accessed via U.S.-only and global strategies. As an investor and manager, our success is firmly rooted in aligning our firm's interests with those of our clients, partners and employees, as well as our commitment to alpha-generating research.



Investment Philosophy
CenterSquare Investment Management executes real asset investment strategies with a focus on market leading research and underwriting methods to identify mispriced investment opportunities. Within the publicly listed real estate and infrastructure markets, our investment approach includes top-down market/country selection and bottom-up underwriting of properties, companies and management teams. In private equity real estate, we focus on crafting unique options for repositioning special situation investments in middle-market real estate across the U.S.



Leadership Team
CenterSquare Investment Management is led by Chief Executive Officer and Chief Investment Officer E. Todd Briddell, with responsibility for overseeing the firm’s real asset investment advisory services including private equity real estate and listed real estate and infrastructure across the United States, Europe and Asia. CenterSquare’s Private Equity Real Estate group is led by David Rabin, and its Listed Real Estate group is led by Dean Frankel and Andrew Nicholas, Global Co-Heads of Real Estate Securities. CenterSquare’s Listed Infrastructure group is led by Portfolio Manager Ted Brooks. CenterSquare has an extensive support team of portfolio managers and analysts to support this leadership team and assist in investment management decisions.











			E. Todd Briddell, CFA
		

			Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer, CenterSquare
		











			Scott Crowe
		

			Chief Investment Strategist, CenterSquare 
		











			Frank J. Ferro
		

