Capital Markets

Company Overview of CenterSquare Investment Management Holdings, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
CenterSquare Investment Management Holdings, Inc. formerly known as Urdang Capital Management Inc. is a real estate investment firm specializing in investments in public real estate securities and private real estate. The firm seeks to make value added and core private real estate investments in office, retail, multifamily, and industrial sectors. For value added real estate investments it focuses on strategies such as lease-up, redevelopment, mark to market, adaptive re-use, repositioning, expansion, pad-site build out, and other strategies such as recapitalization, acquisition partnership interest, participating mortgages, mezzanine debt, and ground up development. For core real estate inv...
CenterSquare Investment Management Holdings, Inc. formerly known as Urdang Capital Management Inc. is a real estate investment firm specializing in investments in public real estate securities and private real estate. The firm seeks to make value added and core private real estate investments in office, retail, multifamily, and industrial sectors. For value added real estate investments it focuses on strategies such as lease-up, redevelopment, mark to market, adaptive re-use, repositioning, expansion, pad-site build out, and other strategies such as recapitalization, acquisition partnership interest, participating mortgages, mezzanine debt, and ground up development. For core real estate investments the firm focuses on class A and B+ product, major metropolitan areas, functional properties with multi-tenant flexibility, credit tenancy, minimum short-term lease roll, total capitalization of $20 million and $75 million, and leverage typically below 50 percent loan to cost and attributes such as Class A/B+, multi-tenant, credit tenants, 9'+ ceiling heights, ample parking, fully sprinklered, modern, functional, devisable, low office buildout, spacious truck court/parking, grocery anchored centers, single-story, strong sales/sf, 5/1000 parking, rich amenity package, and high-end finishes. For both value added and core investments, it focuses on investments in 100,000 SF plus for office, 250,000 SF for industrial/flex, 75,000 SF plus for Retail, and 100 plus units for multi-family sectors. The firm invests in private and public equity real estate markets across the globe with a focus on major US real estate markets. It prefers direct investment, but also consider joint ventures with operating partners with sponsor equity commitment between 10 percent and 25 percent with an average holding period between three and five years with a target of total capitalization of 65 percent. The firm provides its services to high net worth individuals, proprietary accounts, banks or thrift institutions, corporate pension and profit sharing plans, public/ governmental pension plans, Taft-Hartley plans, 401(k) Plans, trusts, charitable institutions, foundations, endowments, municipalities, U.S. registered investment companies, U.S. private investment funds, UCITS, other non-US regulated funds, and other U.S. and international institutions. It manages separate client-focused equity real estate portfolios. The firm invests in diversified portfolio of real estate securities, such as REITs and REOCs to make its public equity investments. It primarily invests in value stocks. It employs fundamental analysis along with combination of bottom-up and top-down stock picking approach to create its portfolios. CenterSquare Investment Management Holdings, Inc. was founded in 1987 and is based in Plymouth Meeting, Pennsylvania with additional office in Newport Beach, California. It operates as a subsidiary of BNY Mellon Asset Management.
